snippet: Robert P. McCulloch, the St. Louis County prosecuting attorney, apologized for failing to immediately make public all documents tied to the grand jury’s decision in the Michael Brown case.
abstract: St Louis prosecutor Robert P McCulloch releases third set of documents tied to grand jury's decision not to indict white police officer in death of unarmed black teenager in Ferguson, Mo; included are transcripts of interviews by law enforcement officials with people who witnessed shooting of Michael Brown, many of whom give conflicting accounts.
lead_paragraph: Robert P. McCulloch, the St. Louis County prosecuting attorney, apologized for failing to immediately make public all documents tied to the grand jury’s decision in the Michael Brown case.

headline.main: More Files Are Released in Shooting in Ferguson
headline.print_headline: More Files Are Released in Shooting in Ferguson
